    <!-- Travel Tips Section -->
    <section class="destinations" id="destinations">
        <h2>Essential Travel Tips</h2>
        <div class="tips">
            <div class="tip">
                <h3>Pack Light, Travel Right</h3>
                <p>Always pack versatile clothing items that can be mixed and matched. Remember: you can do laundry on the road! A lighter bag means easier mobility and less stress during your journey.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip">
                <h3>Book Flights on Tuesdays</h3>
                <p>Airlines often release deals early in the week. Tuesday afternoons typically offer the best prices for both domestic and international flights. Set up price alerts to catch the best deals!</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip">
                <h3>Stay Hydrated and Healthy</h3>
                <p>Carry a reusable water bottle and maintain proper hydration, especially during flights. Pack a small first-aid kit with essential medications and always have travel insurance for peace of mind.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip">
                <h3>Learn Basic Local Phrases</h3>
                <p>Even knowing simple words like "hello," "thank you," and "excuse me" in the local language can greatly enhance your travel experience and show respect for the local culture.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="tip">
                <h3>Download Offline Maps</h3>
                <p>Save data and never get lost by downloading maps of your destination before you leave. Google Maps allows you to save areas for offline use, which is invaluable when exploring new cities.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

